title: ASX to drop, Wall St slips ahead of debate
summary: Australian shares are set to drop at the open amid cautious trading in Europe and New York. Oil fell sharply. The $A advanced.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, global equities rally
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by a rally in global equities. $A higher. Gold, oil and iron ore advance.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise after US tech rallies again
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by a solid buy-the-dip rally in New York, and the $A is flirting with US69¢.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, Wall St ends higher after wild swings
summary: Australian shares are set to open modestly higher to end a volatile week. The Dow fell at the open, surged, fell, surged higher, turned negative and then positive.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, Dow sheds 525 points, $A plunges
summary: Australian shares are set to drop amid renewed, and broad, selling on Wall Street. The $A plunged below US71¢. Gold shed 2%. Iron ore fell 3%.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, $A drops as greenback rallies
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by Amazon. The currency took it on the chin after unexpectedly hawkish comments from one US policymaker.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, Wall St sinks on selloff
summary: Australian shares are poised to plunge 1 per cent at the open amid a broad global selloff. Iron ore, oil and gold fall. $A slides.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slide, Wall St volatility expected to rise
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower with investors expected to accelerate profit taking amid heightening US political risks.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, Wall St dented again by mega techs
summary: Australian shares appear poised to open higher, helped by buying late in New York that cut into an otherwise losing session.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, Powell disappoints, US techs selloff
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower after the US central bank chairman tipped risks to the economic recovery and amid a renewed US tech share selloff.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, US central bank in focus
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher. US stocks ended modestly higher as investors await the outcome of a Federal Reserve policy meeting.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, Wall St rises
summary: Australian shares appear set for a muted open. Wall St rallies broadly. RBA board minutes pending. Oracle's TikTok deal.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, central banks in focus
summary: Australian shares are set for a modest start to the week, during which investors will be parsing policymaker comments from Australia to the UK and the US.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall as selling returns to Wall St
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, as the selloff of US tech shares took Wall Street lower. $A slips.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Wall St rebounds, Tesla rises 11pc
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher after US investors recovered from their latest 'panic attack'. $A up 1pc. Gold, oil rise. Iron ore lower.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, US tech rout deepens, Tesla sheds 21pc
summary: Australian shares are set to drop as the selling of US tech shares yet again hammered Wall St. Tesla plunged after failing to make the S&P 500 and after GM bought a stake in Nikola. $A tumbles.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Trump lashes out at China
summary: Australian shares are poised to rise, bolstered by gains across Europe. Positive sentiment could be checked by Trump's decoupling comments.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slide on extended correction
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower, although the pace of losses is expected to be far more moderate than Friday's rout.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to plunge; Wall St drops on mega-tech selloff
summary: Technology shares fell sharply, dragging all three major US benchmarks lower. The Dow shed 808 points. ASX futures plunged 2.1pc.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, US stocks extend gains
summary: Australian shares are poised to follow Wall Street higher amid a broad rally. The $A dropped. Iron ore rallied.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge higher, GDP data ahead
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, boosted by late gains on Wall Street. $A slips. Second-quarter GDP on Wednesday's agenda.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to slide on first day of September
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, the currency briefly topped US74¢. RBA expected to hold cash rate. Tesla surges.
author: Timothy Moore
